description._content: "Wednesday April 11th. Had a short drive in the afternoon towards the northern end of the island. The forests of pine trees scattered around the old time dwelling houses, and the smooth nature of the turf beneath them, presents the appearance of park lands, and this impression remains with one in whatever direction the visitor travels." - Journal of a Trip to Norfolk Island by Frank Walker R.A.H.S, April 1917. This image is part of a collection entitled 'Views of Norfolk Island', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel.
